ow easy it is to guess that the author’s name is a pseudonym, that the author is not a man! Every sentence of yours buttons to the left. Your predilection for such expressions as “time passed” or “cuddled up frileusement in Mother’s shawl,” the inevitable appearance of an episodic ensign (straight from imitations of War and Peace) who pronounces the letter r as a hard g, and, finally, footnotes with translations of French clichés, afford sufficient indication of your literary skill.